                type="document" xml:id="d697">
                <head>No. 697<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>In his diary notes for October 8, President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                        >Eisenhower</persName> discussed Japan as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In Japan there seems to be some hope that the Japanese will attempt to
                            pick up some of the load and establish their own security organization.
                            Their Constitution, adopted under General <persName corresp="#p_MDII1"
                                >MacArthur</persName>’s supervision, denies them the right to have
                            military forces. But the time has come when they must become responsible
                            for their own internal defense, even though to avoid frightening our
                            other friends in the Pacific, we must always provide the naval and air
                            strength required in that region by the free world.” (<persName
                                corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> Library,
                                <persName>Whitman</persName> file, <gloss target="#t_DDE1"
                                >DDE</gloss> Diaries)</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
